          <text>
                    <body>
                              <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>, <date>June 15,
                                                  B 49</date></p>
                              <p>
                                        <hi rend="underline">32 C</hi>
                              </p>
                              <p><addressee>Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
                              <p>Dear Sir:</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I have withdrawn from the fold of Jewish
                                        literature in<lb/> your favor and I hope we will remain to
                                        be friends or perhaps<lb/> become friends.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I write to urge you to attach my Hebrew Catalogue
                                        to<lb/> your Occident. I would send you by express the
                                        necessary copies.<lb/> I furthermore <sic>askyou</sic> to
                                        forward me by return mail six of your<lb/> Tefilloth with
                                        English translation for German and Polish Jews.<lb/> I have
                                        sold five. If you have some in dark maroquin leather or<lb/>
                                        more expensive copies send two of <sic>themand</sic> four
                                        for $2.50.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I ask you again to do something, even if it is
                                        something<lb/> small for my publishing company and to give
                                        me your orders. It<lb/> would be well, if you would do it
                                        soon for I may not have on hand<lb/> what you need and may
                                        have to send for it. Or it may be necessary to<lb/> have it
                                        bound.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Do you know somebody who wants to sell German type
                                        at<lb/> a reasonable price? I need such type right away.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">Yours very truly,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">
                                        <persName role="author">ISIDOR BUSH</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>Addressed: <addressee>Revd. Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>, Editor of
                                        the Occident, etc. etc.<lb/>
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia, Pa.</placeName></p>
                    </body>
